{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"10008","heading":"State reports","label":"10008 State reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/ch80","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the uses of funds provided under this chapter within the State;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"how the State distributed the funds it received under this chapter;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number of jobs that the Governor estimates were saved or created with funds the State received under this chapter;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"tax increases that the Governor estimates were averted because of the availability of funds from this chapter;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the State’s progress in reducing inequities in the distribution of highly qualified teachers, in implementing a State longitudinal data system, and in developing and implementing valid and reliable assessments for limited English proficient students and children with disabilities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the tuition and fee increases for in-State students imposed by public institutions of higher education in the State during the period of availability of funds under this chapter, and a description of any actions taken by the State to limit those increases;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the extent to which public institutions of higher education maintained, increased, or decreased enrollment of in-State students, including students eligible for Pell Grants or other need-based financial assistance; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t20/s10008","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft20%2Fs10008%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of each modernization, renovation and repair project funded, which shall include the amounts awarded and project costs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
